narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Gender Lab is a unique space where I am able to thoughtfully and deeply engage with my own research and that of my colleagues. I get concrete advise when I present, which definitely improves the quality of my work. I also love to learn about other, related areas research when my peers are presenting.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: This lab provides a level of feedback and constructive criticism that I can't get anywhere else. However, something I've noticed is that when I'm giving feedback on other people's work, I tend to assume that they know their work is great - and therefore focus on areas that could be improved. When *I'm* presenting and receive criticism, however, it's hard to remember that there are also aspects of my research that are interesting and important. I think our lab has started to focus more on what's great about each other's research, and I would love to continue this next year.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Absolutely! I have, indeed, recommended the lab to my peers.
